The President held a meeting to discuss the U.S. Government's efforts to support security for the Olympic Games in Sochi. The United States has offered its full support to Russian authorities, who are responsible for the Games. The President was briefed on the security environment, cooperation with Russian authorities, and U.S. Government support for athletes and Americans attending the Olympics. He directed his team to continue working closely with the Russian Government and other partners to ensure a secure and successful event. The meeting was attended by Vice President Biden, National Security Advisor Rice, and other senior members of the President's team.